        <abstract> 
<p>Gives up plan to have Haeckel’s <hi rend="italic">Generelle morphologie</hi> translated.</p>  
<p>His big book [<hi rend="italic">Variation</hi>] has gone to printer. Thinks of adding a chapter on man.</p>  
<p>Will order Duke of Argyll’s book [<hi rend="italic">Reign of law</hi> (1867)].</p> 
            <p>"Nature never made species mutually sterile [by selection]; nor will man.–"</p>
        </abstract>
